Content of this directory					4-Dec-1995

==============================================================================

MPEG-1 Audio Compliance Data
============================

The MPEG test bitstreams are test patterns (encoded bitstreams, 
generated by a reference encoder and the corresponding decoded 
PCM output, generated by a reference decoder) for conformance 
testing of an ISO/MPEG decoder implementation according to the 
ISO/IEC international standard IS 11172, part 3 - audio). 
The conformance testing is described in part 4 of this standard.


Since this standard consists of three layers, there are different
test patterns for each of these layers which can be found in 
separate files, each of which contains a readme file with 
further information. 

Test patterns for ISO/MPEG Audio Decoders
(Layer I, Layer II and Layer III)

	README		- This file
	layer1.readme	- Information about Layer 1 test patterns
	layer1.tar.gz	- Layer 1 test patterns (tared and gziped)
	layer2.readme	- Information about Layer 2 test patterns
	layer2.tar.gz	- Layer 2 test patterns (tared and gziped)
	layer3.readme	- Information about Layer 3 test patterns
	layer3.tar.gz	- Layer 3 test patterns (tared and gziped)


The data has been produced by:

- Layer 1:   Philips CE, Eindhoven, THE NETHERLANDS
	     Contact: L. van de Kerkhof, 
	     email: vdkerkhof@nlvxe2.ce.philips.nl

- Layer 2:   Institut fuer Rundfunktechnik (IRT), Muenchen, GERMANY
	     Contact: G. Stoll, 
	     email: stoll@irt.de

- Layer 3:   Fraunhofer IIS, Erlangen, GERMANY
	     Contact: K. Brandenburg, 
	     email: bdg@iis.fhg.de

